No, I think this a new bug. The fix is to move those two functions in hlo_matchers.h out of line --- currently they are defined in the header which causes a duplicate definition. I'll fix it but it will take a day or two to make it to Github.

(Apologies for the breakage. Sadly our Mac continuous build doesn't build XLA yet because of limited resources, and this linking problem doesn't show up on Linux.)

No, I think this a new bug. The fix is to move those two functions in hlo_matchers.h out of line --- currently they are defined in the header which causes a duplicate definition. I'll fix it but it will take a day or two to make it to Github.

(Apologies for the breakage. Sadly our Mac continuous build doesn't build XLA yet because of limited resources, and this linking problem doesn't show up on Linux.)
